{
  "stem": "24885.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He wanted just-- as a matter of fact, there were 20 or 30 of them and just eight or 10 escaped.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because they didn't trust their own even then, some of them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because some of them cooperated with the Germans, some Russians.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "As soon as this happened, they took us and put us into the small ghetto, which we called at the time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There we stayed about two months approximately, maybe six weeks, and we wanted to go and work for some place.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And there was a place called [NON-ENGLISH]-- it was a supply house which they supplied food for the SS, and for other German outfits I assume-- but mostly for the SS.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They put us in there in 1943.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And about four months later, the man who was in charge of the German SS men picked me out to work in the food warehouse.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Why, I don't know, but he picked me out of the whole group.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Well, we had food in there because it was a food warehouse-- that they gave us the leftover, and so on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But they worked us hard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Well, in the food warehouse, of course, was much easier.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I worked inside.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I can remember I smuggled out a salami, like down here, tied it with a little string.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Walked outside to the outhouse where they were working, and my brother knew, and I tied it inside.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I put the nail in, and he came in afterwards and took the salami out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I mean that's it's the things we innovated how to survive.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
